<Hds::Tabs as |T|>
  <T.Tab>About</T.Tab>
  <T.Tab>Support</T.Tab>
  <T.Tab>Contributing</T.Tab>
  <T.Panel>
    <div class="doc-Page">
      <div class="doc-Page-content">
        <p>Consul UI Toolkit is a collection of presentational components and
          utilities specifically meant to be shared across the different Consul
          applications. The toolkit contains generic components that you may
          have come to expect from a component library, as well as very feature
          specific components meant for the Consul apps</p>

        <p>While the toolkit is an open-source project, it is intentionally
          built for Consul products. However, it may be used outside of them.
          Please refer to the
          <Hds::Link::Inline
            @href="https://github.com/hashicorp/consul-ui-toolkit/blob/main/LICENSE"
          >License</Hds::Link::Inline>
          before using the toolkit in your own projects.</p>

        <h2 id="compatibility">Compatibility</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Ember.js v3.28 or above</li>
          <li>Embroider or ember-auto-import v2</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>
        <CodeBlock @code="ember install @hashicorp/consul-ui-toolkit" />
      </div>
      <InPageNav as |I|>
        <I.Link @section="#compatibility" @depth={{1}}>Compatibility</I.Link>
        <I.Link @section="#installation" @depth={{1}}>Installation</I.Link>
      </InPageNav>

    </div>
  </T.Panel>
  <T.Panel>

    <div class="doc-Page">
      <div class="doc-Page-content">
        <Hds::Alert @type="inline" @color="highlight" as |A|>
          <A.Title>
            Many resources and links on this page are only available to
            HashiCorp employees.
          </A.Title>
        </Hds::Alert>

        <p>We’re happy to provide support to HashiCorp product teams that use
          Consul UI Toolkit. Use these resources to get help.</p>

        <h2 id="live-support">Live support</h2>
        <p>Join the
          <Hds::Link::Inline
            @href="https://hashicorp.slack.com/archives/C9X0VGJNL/p1681481135411859"
          >#team-consul-ui</Hds::Link::Inline>
          Slack channel to ask questions, request and provide feedback, or start
          a conversation with our team. As a globally-distributed team, there
          may be a slight delay in answering some questions, but we’re committed
          to responding in a timely manner.</p>

        <h2 id="file-issue">File an issue</h2>
        <p>Find a bug? Want to report a security issue?
          <Hds::Link::Inline
            @href="https://github.com/hashicorp/consul-ui-toolkit/issues/new"
          >File an issue in our GitHub repository</Hds::Link::Inline></p>
      </div>
      <InPageNav as |I|>
        <I.Link @section="#live-support">Live support</I.Link>
        <I.Link @section="#file-issue">File an issue</I.Link>
      </InPageNav>
    </div>
  </T.Panel>
  <T.Panel>
    <div class="doc-Page">
      <div class="doc-Page-content">
        <Hds::Alert @type="inline" @color="highlight" as |A|>
          <A.Title>At this time we are not accepting external contributions from
            non-HashiCorp employees. Many resources and links on this page are
            only available to HashiCorp employees.
          </A.Title>
        </Hds::Alert>
        <h2 id="contribution-types">Types of contribution</h2>
        <p>At this time we are not accepting contributions of new components
          from outside of the Consul team. We do welcome contributions in the
          following forms:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><Hds::Link::Inline
              @href="https://github.com/hashicorp/consul-ui-toolkit/issues/new"
            >Reporting</Hds::Link::Inline>
            and
            <Hds::Link::Inline
              @href="https://github.com/hashicorp/consul-ui-toolkit/compare"
            >fixing</Hds::Link::Inline>
            bugs</li>
          <li>Improving documentation</li>
          <li>Participating in discussions in our
            <Hds::Link::Inline
              @href="https://hashicorp.slack.com/archives/C9X0VGJNL/p1681481135411859"
            >team slack channel</Hds::Link::Inline></li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="code-contributions">Code contributions</h2>
        <p>For contributions to either the toolkit or documentation, consult the
          <Hds::Link::Inline
            @href="https://github.com/hashicorp/consul-ui-toolkit/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md"
          >CONTRIBUTING.md</Hds::Link::Inline>
          file.</p>
      </div>
      <InPageNav as |I|>
        <I.Link @section="contribution-types">Types of contribution</I.Link>
        <I.Link @section="code-contributions">Code contributions</I.Link>
      </InPageNav>
    </div>
  </T.Panel>
